613 ON TOWARD THE GOAL PRESS ON ALONE  YET UNAFRAID
1 “On toward the goal!” Press on! Alone, yet unafraid;  He cut the path, who beckons thee, On then, and undismayed. 
2 “On toward the goal!” Press on! The eyes that are a flame  Are watching thee, what then are men? What matter praise, or  blame? 
3 “On toward the goal!” Press on! Look not behind thee now,  When just ahead lies His “Well done,” And crowns await thy brow. 
4 “On toward the goal!” Press on! Blind, deaf and sometimes dumb  Along the blood-marked, uphill way, Hard after Christ, press on!
