11.9.11.9. WITH CHORUS 
The Gospel 
1 Oh, how dark the night that wrapt my spirit round!  Oh, how deep the woe my Savior found 
 When He walked across the waters of my soul, 
 Bade my night disperse and made me whole! 
(C) All the way to Calvary He went for me, 
 He went for me, He went for me; 
 All the way to Calvary He went for me, 
 He died to set me free. 
2 Tremblingly a sinner bowed before His face, 
 Naught I knew of pardon, God’s free grace; 
 Heard a voice so melting, “Cease thy wild regret,  Jesus bought thy pardon, paid thy debt.” 
3 O ‘twas wondrous love the Savior showed for me!  When He left His throne for Calvary, 
 When He bore my trespass, bore it all alone; 
 Praise His Name forever, make it known. 
672 我听救主声音
1 我听救主声音，  说我能力薄弱，  若非诚心相信，  不能免去罪过。
和 我欠千万金，  主替我还清；  一生犯罪真苦辛，  主今赦免、怜悯。 
2 主，我今才看明，  惟你有这力量，  能洗污秽洁净，  使软弱变刚强。 
3 我真没有善良，  可以得主救恩；  但主特别体谅，  用爱救我罪人。 
4 将来立在神前，  神必不再追问；  因主为我亏欠，  已经流血受审。 
672 I HEAR THE SAVIOR SAY
1 I hear the Savior say, 
 “Thy strength indeed is small,  Child of weakness, watch and pray,  Find in Me thine all in all.” 
(C) Jesus paid it all, 
 All to Him I owe; 
 Sin had left a crimson stain, 
 He washed it white as snow. 
2 Lord, now indeed I find 
 Thy pow’r, and Thine alone, 
 Can change the leper’s spots, 
 And melt the heart of stone. 
3 For nothing good have I 
 Whereby Thy grace to claim —   I’ll wash my garments white 
 In the blood of Calv’ry’s Lamb. 
4 And when, before the throne, 
 I stand in Him complete, 
 “Jesus died my soul to save,” 
 My lips shall still repeat.

673 哎呀救主真曾流血
1 哎呀！救主真曾流血？ 
 真曾舍命亡躬？ 
 祂肯牺牲祂的超越， 
 为我这个小虫？ 
和 在十架，在十架，我看见主恩光，  罪重担从我身全卸脱！ 
 在十架，我因信，眼明亮，心平康，  我终日能欢乐！ 
2 祂在木上那样哀叹， 
 可是为我罪愆？ 
 怜悯何满！慈爱何泛！ 
 恩典何其无边！ 
3 难怪太阳立变暗乌， 
 隐藏一切荣光； 
 当神基督造物的主， 
 为人担罪而亡。 
4 当我看见祂十字架， 
 也当隐藏羞脸； 
 心当溶化，发出感嗟， 
 眼当流类自贬。 
5 但这满腔忧伤 
 不能稍还主爱的债； 
 主，我在此奉上一生， 
 聊表此心感戴。 
673 ALAS AND DID MY SAVIOR BLEED
1 Alas, and did my Savior bleed? 
 And did my Sovereign die? 
 Would He devote that sacred head 
 For such a worm as I? 
(C) At the cross, at the cross where I first saw the light,  And the burden of my heart rolled away,  It was there by faith I received my sight,  And now I am happy all the day! 
2 Was it for sins that I had done 
 He groaned upon the tree? 
 Amazing pity! grace unknown! 
 And love beyond degree! 
3 Well might the sun in darkness hide, 
 And shut His glories in, 
 When Christ, the mighty Maker, died 
 For man, His creature’s sin. 
4 Thus might I hide my blushing face 
 While His dear cross appears. 
 Dissolve my heart in thankfulness, 
 And melt mine eyes to tears. 
5 But drops of grief can ne’er repay 
 The debt of love I owe; 
 Here, Lord, I give myself away, 
 ‘Tis all that I can do.
674 我为什么忧惧疑惑
1 我为什么忧惧、疑惑？  神岂未曾将我罪过  归祂儿子身上？ 
 主所为我还清的债，  公义的神能否再来  要我重新清偿？ 
2 我们所有罪戾；
 神的忿怒不能威胁，  因我已经洒上宝血，  靠恩已经称义。 
3 罪债一起清算；
 神就不会两面讨债：  先在我的中保身上….   后又要我归还。 
4 我的心哪，应当安息，  你的救主所有功绩，  已使你得开释； 
 当信祂的有效宝血，  不怕神再将你弃绝，  因主已为你死。 
674 WHY SHOULD I WORRY DOUBT AND FEAR
1 Why should I worry, doubt and fear? 
 Has God not caused His Son to bear 
 My sins upon the tree? 
 The debt that Christ for me has paid, 
 Would God another mind have made 
 To claim again from me? 
2 Redemption full the Lord has made, 
 And all my debts has fully paid, 
 From law to set me free. 
 I fear not for the wrath of God, 
 For I’ve been sprinkled with His blood, 
 It wholly covers me. 
3 For me forgiveness He has gained,  
 And full acquittal was obtained, 
 All debts of sin are paid; 
 God would not have His claim on two, 
 First on His Son, my Surety true, 
 And then upon me laid. 
4 So now I have full peace and rest, 
 My Savior Christ hath done the best 
 And set me wholly free; 
 By His all-efficacious blood 
 I ne’er could be condemned by God, 
 For He has died for me!
