676 NOTHING EITHER GREAT OR SMALL
1 Nothing either great or small —  
 Nothing, sinner, no; 
 Jesus did it, did it all, 
 Long, long ago. 
(C) “It is finished!” yes, indeed, 
 Finished every jot: 
 Sinner, this is all you need —  
 Tell me, is it not? 
2 When He, from His lofty throne, 
 Stooped to do and die, 
 Everything was fully done; 
 Hearken to His cry: 
3 Weary, working, burdened one, 
 Wherefore toil you so? 
 Cease your doing; all was done 
 Long, long ago. 
4 Till to Jesus’ work you cling 
 By a simple faith, 
 “Doing” is a deadly thing —  
 “Doing” ends in death. 
5 Down at Jesus’ feet;  Stand in Him, in Him alone, Gloriously complete.
