 Come in and take full control.
711 我今信靠你主耶稣
1 我今信靠你，主耶稣，  单单信靠你； 
 为这完全、白白救赎，  信靠你。 
2 为得赦免，我信靠你，  俯伏你脚前； 
 信靠你的慈祥、 
 怜恤和恩典。 
3 为蒙洗净，我信靠你，  你已流宝血； 
 这血为要将我 
 洗涤成圣洁。 
4 我信靠你必引导我，  惟你来引领； 
 天天、时刻，无论什么，  都供应。 
5 因你能力，我信靠你，  你永不负我； 
 你自己所赐的话语，  永稳妥。 
6 主耶稣，我今信靠你，  你必保守我； 
 我要永远将我自己，  全信托。 
711 I AM TRUSTING THEE LORD JESUS
1 I am trusting Thee, Lord Jesus, 
 Trusting only Thee; 
 Trusting Thee for full salvation, 
 Great and free. 
2 I am trusting Thee for pardon, 
 At Thy feet I bow; 
 For Thy grace and tender mercy, 
 Trusting now. 
3 I am trusting Thee for cleansing 
 In the crimson flood; 
 Trusting Thee to make me holy 
 By Thy blood. 
4 I am trusting Thee to guide me; 
 Thou alone shalt lead, 
 Every day and hour supplying 
 All my need. 
5 I am trusting Thee for power, 
 Thine can never fail; 
 Words which Thou Thyself shalt give me  Must prevail. 
6 I am trusting Thee, Lord Jesus; 
 Never let me fall; 
 I am trusting Thee for ever, 
 And for all.
712 耶稣我信靠你
1 耶稣，我信靠你，  全心信靠你； 
 失迷、无助、内疚，  你将我拯救； 
 别无救主像你， 
 在天或在地； 
 你为罪人受死， 
 好使我免死。 
和 耶稣，我信靠你，  全心信靠你！ 
 失迷、无助、内疚，  你将我拯救。 
2 我必信靠耶稣， 
 思念你道路； 
 在地三十三载， 
 满有怜与爱： 
 罪人乐就近你， 
 病人来投倚； 
 无人被你厌弃， 
 因你恩无极。 
3 耶稣，我信靠你，  信靠你话语， 
 你的慈怜声音， 
 前我未曾闻； 
 现因你灵教导， 
 何甜美味道！ 
 惟愿坐你脚前， 
 聆听你圣言。 
4 耶稣，我信靠你，  丝毫不怀疑； 
 不论何人来倚， 
 你总不丢弃； 
 你应许真可靠， 
 你血有功效！ 
 这是我的救恩， 
 我的救主神！ 
712 JESUS I WILL TRUST THEE
1 Jesus, I will trust Thee, 
 Trust Thee with my soul, 
 Guilty, lost and helpless, 
 Thou canst make me whole: 
 There is none in heaven 
 Or on earth like Thee: 
 Thou hast died for sinners, 
 Therefore, Lord, for me. 
(C) Jesus, I will trust Thee, 
 Trust Thee with my soul, 
 Guilty, lost and helpless, 
 Thou canst make me whole. 
2 Jesus, I must trust Thee, 
 Pondering Thy ways; 
 Full of love and mercy 
 All Thine earthly days: 
 Sinners gathered round Thee, 
 Lepers sought Thy face: 
 None too vile or loathsome 
 For a Savior’s grace. 
3 Jesus, I can trust Thee, 
 Trust Thy written Word, 
 Though Thy voice of pity 
 I have never heard: 
 When Thy Spirit teacheth, 
 To my taste how sweet! 
 Only may I hearken, 
 Sitting at Thy feet. 
4 Jesus, I do trust Thee, 
 Trust without a doubt; 
 Whosoever cometh 
 Thou wilt not cast out: 
 Faithful is Thy promise, 
 Precious is Thy blood: 
 These my soul’s salvation, 
 Thou my Savior God!
713 我爱述说这故事
1 我爱述说这故事，  关乎耶稣降世； 
 祂是神的独生子，  因爱，为人受死。  我爱述说这故事，  因它真实、可颂；  别无一事能如此 
 满足我的情衷。 
和 我爱述说这故事，  直至永世亿万载；  述说老、老的故事，  关乎耶稣的爱。 
2 我爱述说这故事，  美妙令人心倾， 
 远胜最美的幻思，  远胜黄金梦境； 
 我爱述说这故事，  因它益我良多； 
 因我认识它价值，  故今向你述说。 
3 我爱述说这故事，  不厌述说千遍； 
 好像每多说一次，  更多觉它甘甜。  我爱述说这故事，  因多人未听见， 
 这个救恩的启示，  出自神的圣言。 
4 我爱述说这故事，  因人虽常听闻， 
 仍觉饥渴要认识，  一如从未听闻。  那日进入荣耀时，  我所唱新、新诗，  仍是这老、老故事 -   我所久爱不释。 
713 I LOVE TO TELL THE STORY
1 I love to tell the story, 
 Of unseen things above, 
 Of Jesus and His glory, 
 Of Jesus and His love. 
 I love to tell the story, 
 Because I know ‘tis true; 
 It satisfies my longings 
 As nothing else can do. 
(C) I love to tell the story, 
 ‘Twill be my theme in glory 
 To tell the old, old story 
 Of Jesus and His love. 
2 I love to tell the story; 
 More wonderful it seems 
 Than all the golden fancies 
 Of all my golden dreams, 
 I love to tell the story, 
 It did so much for me; 
 And that is just the reason 
 I tell it now to thee. 
3 I love to tell the story; 
 ‘Tis pleasant to repeat 
 What seems each time I tell it, 
 More wonderfully sweet. 
 I love to tell the story; 
 For some have never heard 
 The message of salvation 
 From God’s own holy Word. 
4 I love to tell the story; 
 For those who know it best 
 Seem hungering and thirsting 
 To hear it like the rest. 
 And when, in scenes of glory, 
 I sing the new, new song, 
 ‘Twill be the old, old story, 
 That I have loved so long.
