 Glory to His name.
716 我主耶稣竟然甘心替我受死
1 我主耶稣竟然甘心替我受死，  使不堪如我能得恩典； 
 祂竟甘心走上十架、被钉至死，  使我一生罪孽蒙赦免。 
和 祂在十字架上， 
 将我罪全担当， 
 哦，祂竟甘心为我担当！ 
 祂在十字架上， 
 为我受苦、命丧， 
 祂在彼将我罪全担当。 
2 祂待我满了温柔、慈爱并忍耐，  祂洗净我心中的污秽； 
 祂说：“不再定罪，”我今已被解开，  祂在十架上担我众罪。 
3 我要紧靠救主，永不将祂离弃，  天天欢乐在世作客旅； 
 我口高唱得救乐歌，满心欢喜，  因我众罪已被祂担去。 
716 THERE WAS ONE WHO WAS WILLING TO  DIE IN MY STEAD
12.9.12.9. WITH CHORUS 
The Gospel 
1 There was One who was willing to die in my stead,  That a soul so unworthy might live, 
 And the path to the cross He was willing to tread,  All the sins of my life to forgive. 
(C) They were borne on the cross, 
 They were borne on the cross, 
 O how much He was willing to bear! 
 With what anguish and loss, 
 Jesus went to the cross! 
 But He carried my sins with Him there. 
2 He is tender and loving and patient with me, 
 While He cleanses my heart of its dross; 
 But “there’s no condemnation,” I know I am free,  For my sins were all borne on the cross. 
3 I will cling to my Savior and never depart —  
 I will joyfully journey each day, 
 With a song on my lips and a song in my heart, 
 That my sins have been taken away.
717 当我疲困罪恶境 特.和.
1 当我疲困罪恶境， 
 祂以柔爱来寻， 
 怀我、肩我满温情，  带我归祂羊群； 
 千万天使因此欢腾，  甚至歌声满天回应。 
和 爱何大，寻回我！  血何宝，赎回我！  恩何丰，带回我归羊群！  奇妙恩，带回我归羊群！ 
2 伤重待毙祂见我， 
 便以油、酒敷裹； 
 柔声细语许我说： 
 “你要永远属我！”  从无声音如此甜美，  伤痛之心顿觉欣慰！ 
3 钉痕、枪伤祂示我，  血也、水也流出， 
 头戴荆冕、利刺戳，  羞辱加上痛楚； 
 我真不知我有何长，  使祂为我这样受戕。 
4 我今安坐祂面前， 
 瞻仰祂的荣脸， 
 心觉希奇，灵感赞，  追忆祂的恩眷； 
 似乎永世所有时间，  用来赞祂尚嫌太短。 
5 年日虽然在飞逝， 
 今享完全安息； 
 等候光明的日子， 
 永远与主同居。 
 那时召我到祂身边，  与祂同在，作祂圣伴。 
717 IN TENDERNESS HE SOUGHT ME IRREGULAR METER WITH CHORUS
1 In tenderness He sought me, 
 Weary and sick with sin, 
 And on His shoulders brought me 
 Into His flock again. 
 While angels in His presence sang 
 Until the courts of heaven rang. 
(C) Oh, the love that sought me! 
 Oh, the blood that bought me! 
 Oh, the grace that brought me to the flock,  Wondrous grace that brought me to the flock! 
2 He washed the bleeding sin-wounds, 
 And poured in oil and wine; 
 He whispered to assure me, 
 “I’ve found thee, thou art Mine:” 
 I never heard a sweeter voice, 
 It made my aching heart rejoice. 
3 He pointed to the nail-prints, 
 For me His blood was shed; 
 A mocking crown so thorny, 
 Was placed upon His head: 
 I wondered what He saw in me, 
 To suffer such deep agony. 
4 I’m sitting in His presence, 
 The sunshine of His face, 
 While with adoring wonder 
 His blessings I retrace. 
 It seems as if eternal days 
 Are far too short to sound His praise. 
5 So while the hours are passing, 
 All now is perfect rest; 
 I’m waiting for the morning, 
 The brightest and the best, 
 When He will call us to His side, 
 To be with Him, His spotless Bride.
